Acceptance: A deterministic audit verifies source-manifest hashes, every crosswalk status/evidence/task/doc link, corresponding public/machine coverage, and owned partial follow-ups. Missing input, hash drift, stale path, contradiction, or undocumented capability fails actionably; changed sources/statuses require an explicit dated reviewed manifest/crosswalk receipt update rather than silently regenerating expected output. Canonical contract: docs/plans/2026-07-13-github-user-attribution-and-feature-discovery.md.